	heroObjectPosition={`center top`}
	directAnswerHtml={`<strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">If you're a physician, the Father's Heart Bible™ is for you.</strong> You carry more than your patients ever see — the crushing responsibility for life and death, the perfectionism that never lets up, the exhaustion you push through because someone needs you. The <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Father's Heart Bible™</a> is a fresh English translation you can read and <em>listen to</em> free — between rounds, on the commute, after a hard shift — and it reveals God as a <em>Father</em> from beginning to end. Whether you searched "Bible verses for doctors," "scripture for physicians," or "encouragement for healthcare workers," the answer starts in one place: you hold others' lives in your hands, but you were never meant to be God. You are His beloved child first — fathered before you ever carry anyone else.`}
	keyTakeaway={`You are not the savior you feel you must be. You are the Father's beloved son or daughter — carried, not carrying everything alone. Your worth was never your outcomes, your hours, or your ability to hold it all together.`}
	painsHeading={`The weight doctors carry`}
	painsIntroHtml={`If you feel burned out, emotionally numb, or like you have to be the strong one no matter the cost, you are not weak and you are not alone. The data on physician well-being says the weight out loud.`}
	painStats={[
		{ value: `49%`, label: `of physicians reported at least one symptom of burnout (Mayo Clinic Proceedings, 2023)` },
		{ value: `63%`, label: `of physicians reported burnout at the peak of the pandemic — the highest rate on record (Mayo Clinic Proceedings / AMA, 2022)` },
		{ value: `49%`, label: `of physicians said they feel burned out, with emotional exhaustion the most common driver (Medscape Physician Burnout & Depression Report, 2024)` },
		{ value: `20%`, label: `of physicians reported feeling depressed, and most said it affects their patient interactions (Medscape, 2024)` },
		{ value: `~300 to 400`, label: `physicians are estimated to die by suicide each year in the U.S. — among the highest of any profession (NAM / AFSP)` },
