	verses={[
		{ ref: `Matthew 11:28-30`, slug: `matthew`, ch: 11, text: `Come to Me, all of you who are weary and weighed down, and I will give you rest. Take My yoke and learn from Me, for I am gentle and humble in heart, and you will find rest for your soul — for My yoke is easy and My burden is light.`, note: `After the longest shift, the One who carries everyone invites you to lay it down and rest — not perform.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 121:3-4`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 121, text: `He will not let your foot slip — the One who keeps you will not slumber. See, the One who watches over you will neither slumber nor sleep.`, note: `When you're awake on call, your Father is awake too — keeping you, so you don't have to keep everything yourself.` },
		{ ref: `Isaiah 40:28-31`, slug: `isaiah`, ch: 40, text: `Your Father does not grow tired or weary; He gives strength to the weary and increases the power of the weak. Those who wait on Him will renew their strength; they will soar on wings like eagles, run and not grow weary, walk and not faint.`, note: `Your reserves run out; His never do. He renews the strength burnout drains away.` },
		{ ref: `2 Corinthians 12:9`, slug: `2-corinthians`, ch: 12, text: `My grace is enough for you, for My power is made perfect in weakness. So I will gladly rest in My weakness, that the power of My Father may rest on me.`, note: `You don't have to be invincible. His strength shows up exactly where yours gives out.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 46:1`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 46, text: `Your Father is your refuge and strength, an ever-present help in times of trouble.`, note: `When the code is called and the room moves fast, He is already there — present help, not distant judge.` },
		{ ref: `Proverbs 3:5-6`, slug: `proverbs`, ch: 3, text: `Trust your Father with all your heart, and do not lean on your own understanding; in all your ways acknowledge Him, and He will make your paths straight.`, note: `For the moments medicine can't answer, you can lean on a Father wiser than all your training.` },
		{ ref: `Philippians 4:13`, slug: `philippians`, ch: 4, text: `I can do all things through the One who strengthens me — my Father who gives me power.`, note: `Not your endurance, but His strength carries you through the day you didn't think you could finish.` },
		{ ref: `Isaiah 41:10`, slug: `isaiah`, ch: 41, text: `Do not fear, for I am with you; do not be dismayed, for I am your Father. I will strengthen you and help you; I will uphold you with My righteous right hand.`, note: `When a case frightens you and the weight feels too heavy, He promises to hold you up.` },
		{ ref: `Deuteronomy 33:27`, slug: `deuteronomy`, ch: 33, text: `The eternal Father is your dwelling place, and underneath you are His everlasting arms.`, note: `However far you feel you could fall, His arms are already underneath — you are caught before you drop.` },
	]}
